{
  "id": "019cdcdc-fd00-7850-9bc2-9ea98a406d1a",
  "content": "### Download URL\n\n## Status Display\n\nExtends `show_status()`:\n\n```\n=== Corvia Workspace Services ===\n\n  ollama       enabled=disabled running=no\n  surrealdb    enabled=disabled running=no\n  cuda         enabled=enabled  gpu=NVIDIA RTX 4090 (24GB) driver=555.42\n  corvia       enabled=always   running=yes\n\n  Config: provider=corvia model=nomic-embed-text-v1.5 store=lite\n```\n\nWhen CUDA is disabled or no GPU:\n```\n  cuda         enabled=disabled gpu=not detected\n```\n\n\n## Post-Start Integration\n\nNo special restart logic needed. The binary choice is persistent. Enable/disable scripts kill and restart `corvia-inference` if it's running.\n\n`post-start.sh` already re-enables previously enabled services via the flags file. CUDA flag (`cuda=enabled`) is checked — if set, the CUDA binary is already in place, so no action needed beyond the normal inference server start.\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-04-m4.5-cuda-toggle-design.md",
